Q.  Tell me about a time when you were faced with a problem that had a number of possible solutions.What was the problem and how did 
    you determine the course of action? What was the outcome of that choice?
Ans- related to me: It was my final year in college and i was still struggling what to do next. I did my majors in chemical Engineering
     with minors in software engineering course. I have number of solutions to opt for like go for masters, or mba or go for a job or to 
     go to abroad and settle. Above all choices i decide i want to becomoe Software Engineer because when i look back i always been fascinated with
     Software engineering, like i can talk all day with my cse friends about cs topics, projects and i realise this is the way. Even today
     i feel that was the best decision of my life. Because i am happy doing this
     
